  <name>OpenChamber</name>
  <summary>A rich interface for OpenCode</summary>

  <description>
    <p>
      OpenChamber is a rich graphical interface for the OpenCode coding agent.
      Review diffs, manage agents, run dev servers, and keep the big picture
      while your AI codes — on desktop, browser, or phone.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Branchable chat timeline with undo, redo, and one-click forks from any turn</li>
      <li>Multi-agent runs from one prompt with isolated worktrees</li>
      <li>Smart tool UIs for diffs, file operations, permissions, and task progress</li>
      <li>Full Git workflows in-app: identities, commits, PR creation, checks, merges</li>
      <li>GitHub-native sessions started from issues and pull requests</li>
      <li>Plan/Build mode with a dedicated plan view for drafting implementation steps</li>
      <li>Integrated terminal with per-directory sessions</li>
      <li>Voice mode with speech input and read-aloud responses</li>
      <li>Open In shortcuts for Finder/Files, Terminal, and your preferred editor</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

